title: Ansbach shuts out Baumholder to stay unbeaten
text:
Ansbach shuts out Baumholder to stay unbeaten Baumholder page 
ANSBACH, Germany -- The two extremes of DODDS-Europe Division II football stayed on their disparate paths Friday night as the unbeaten defending champion Ansbach Cougars routed the winless Baumholder Bucs 53-0. 
The game locks Ansbach into the second seed of the upcoming Division II postseason, behind the winner of Saturday's Bitburg-Rota clash. The Cougars will have home-field advantage for next week's quarterfinal round and, if they win, a semifinal game the following week. 
Baumholder ends its season on a 12-game losing streak dating back to 2013. 
Jairiq Leary rushed for 75 yards and a score and Tyler Benton collected 53 rushing yards and a touchdown to pace the Ansbach offense. Dahomey Iglesias had five tackles and a fumble recovery for the Cougars. 
Solo Turgeon gathered 86 yards on seven rushes for Baumholder, while senior Anthony Amos capped his Bucs career with six solo tackles. Join the conversation and share your voice.
